    StringType.split(char delimiter, int limit)
    Splits a string by a given char delimiter and returns an array of substrings matched around it the parameter limit specifies the result threshold: If limit is positive, the delimiter will be applied to at most limit - 1, the rest of the string will be added to the last entry of the array if limit is equal to 0, the delimiter will be applied as many time as possible, removing any trailing empty entries if limit is negative, the delimiter will be applied as many times as possible, while leaving any trailing empty spaces

    Splits a string by a given delimiter and returns an array of substrings matched around the given delimiter, the parameter limit specifies the result threshold: If limit is positive, the delimiter will be applied to at most limit - 1, the rest of the string will be added to the last entry of the array if limit is equal to 0, the delimiter will be applied as many time as possible, removing any trailing empty entries if limit is negative, the delimiter will be applied as many times as possible, while leaving any trailing empty spaces
